Police raided a flat on Anton Lembede Street (Smith Street) in central Durban, and arrested a 48-year-old man, who was found in possession of drugs with an estimated value of more than R360k, on Wednesday afternoon. The arrested suspect appeared in the Durban Magistrate’s Court for possession of drugs.Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said: “His arrest follows an operation that was conducted by police officers from the Provincial Drug and Firearm Unit on Wednesday afternoon at  5pm. The team proceeded to a flat situated on Smith Street and conducted a search. Upon searching the flat, the suspect was found in possession of 1644 pieces of rock cocaine, 10 moons of rock cocaine, 1350 capsules of heroin, mandrax tablet and five plastic packets of cocaine powder weighing 389 grams.” He said cash of R18, 110 suspected to be the proceeds of drugs was also seized by police. The estimated street value of the recovered drugs is R360, 570. A case of possession of drugs was opened at Point SAPS for investigation. “This arrest is testimony that drug operations are in full swing. I am pleased with the recent arrests made to curb the dealing and abuse of drugs as well as other cases in the province,” said the KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula.